label: engagement
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000029
desc: The amount and manner of use of, or interaction with, an invention by a performer

label: display trend
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000128
desc: the general movement over time of a detectable change in performance

label: gap
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000013
desc: A numerical difference between the performance data of a performer for a performance measure and some comparator.

label: multiple performer display
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000112
desc: A multi-performer display is a performance summary display that represents two or more performers.

label: performer cardinality
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000123
desc: the number of dimensions that represent performers in a display

label: relational information display
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000030
desc: A display which represents relations between dimensions.

label: performance report
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000014
desc: A report contain information about performer(s) performance datum for performance measure(s), and which is delivered to a recipient

label: time cardinality
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000124
desc: the number of dimensions that represent time in a display

label: normative information
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000052
desc: Definition Needed

label: performance level
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000042
desc: The subjective evaluation about the quality (low, satisfactory, or high) of performance data for a performer on a given performance measure, or set of measures

label: intervention features
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000026
desc: features of an interventions that are likely to produce an interaction

label: comparator
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000037
desc: A performer to which a performance report is not delivered, and to which a recipient can be compared

label: negative performance trend
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000130
desc: A trend where the direction of change is negative

label: high performance
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000043
desc: A contextually defined performance level that is considered high.

label: single performer display
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000111
desc: A single-performer display is a performance summary display that represents a performer.

label: display dimension cardinality
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000122
desc: The number of represented dimensions in a display

label: satisfactory performance
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000040
desc: An acceptable performance level

label: performance datum
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000003
desc: A documented outcome of the targeted behavior that results from processes such as performance measurement, prediction, or goal-setting.

label: prevention framing
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000116
desc: An attribute of an intervention that exposes loss

label: low performance
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000044
desc: A contextually defined performance level that is considered low

label: minimally sufficient data
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000041
desc: The smallest quantity of data from which meaningful inferences and/or evaluations can be made.

label: significant change in performance
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000039
desc: A contextually defined notable amount of change in a performer's performance data, or as compared to comparator, for a performance measure.

label: recipient
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000036
desc: the performer to which a performance report is delivered in order to enact a feedback intervention

label: promotion framing
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000117
desc: an attribute of an intervention that exposes gain

label: performer
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000001
desc: A continuant to which observed or expected performance information can be attributed, including healthcare professionals, teams and organizations that are the recipients of a report, as well as benchmarks, standards, and goals that are applied as performance comparators.

label: performance
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000139
desc: a determinable quality that is dependant on human beings organizations and instantiated by measurement values of a behavior process

label: positive performance trend
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000129
desc: Definition Needed

label: data features
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000023
desc: Aspects of data that indicate its appropriateness for various types of feedback interventions.

label: relational information display template
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000133
desc: the specifications and metadata associated with a relational information display

label: uptake
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000028
desc: The presence of some level of engagement with an intervention by a target performer

label: usage
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000027
desc: The uptake and engagement with an intervention by a performer.

label: message framing
subject: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/psdo#psdo_0000038
desc: An intervention attribute through which information is exposed, as to affect a particular emotional response
